<!--
  CREATION templates for the Mughal succession emperors (the 1707 cascade). These MUST live under
  the NPCCharacters node (same schema as vanilla lords.xml) — that is the only schema that declares
  culture/skill_template/occupation and actually instantiates a hero. The companion <Hero> entries in
  heroes.xml (Heroes node, override-only) supply faction + parentage + bio and DRIVE creation against
  these templates. (A Heroes entry with no matching template here -> "Null object reference"/crash.)

  Faces use BodyProperty face_key_template (age-appropriate procedural Mughal features) rather than a
  hand-authored face key — exact historical likeness needs face codes from the in-game editor. Each
  reuses the vanilla empire KING equipment set (battle + civilian; the civilian set is MANDATORY —
  a missing civilian EquipmentSet native-crashes at world-gen).
-->
<NPCCharacters>

	<!-- Aurangzeb's FACE is borrowed verbatim from the vanilla character Unqid (the Aserai sultan,
	     vanilla lord_3_1) — a turbaned, bearded older ruler face fitting a Mughal emperor. Baked key +
	     face_mesh_cache="true" so it renders exactly as Unqid's; aserai hair/beard tags match it. -->
